{"id": "1517376087141908551", "channel_id": "1517376087141908551", "type": 0, "author_id": "702430527994724432", "author_name": "ice3564", "author_bot": false, "content": "Right now, once story/event content is cleared, it can feel like there is not enough content to keep testing teams and strategies every day. I think a mode like an Endless Tower / Abyss Challenge / Infinite Expedition would fit Morimens very well.\n\nFor example:\n\nPlayers climb stages with increasing difficulty, and every few floors could have special rules, enemy modifiers, or sanity-related effects. Each stage/floor can be short like W3 or W4 in D-tide. This would give players a reason to build different Awakeners, experiment with decks, and keep improving their account even outside limited-time events.\n\nIt does not need to be very reward-heavy. Even small weekly or monthly rewards, ranking badges, cosmetics, profile frames, or achievement-based rewards would be enough. The main value would be giving players a permanent place to enjoy the combat system and test their teams.\n\nYou might argue there is Arcade mode to play but after you cleared it a few time, which I did and already maxed out HSR lvl, the rest are repetitive. I can even remember most miniboss/boss variation in the stage. And there is no fun to keep bullying the boss you already beat. \n\nWhat would be good for player mental health is something that bring a breath of fresh air. Different enemies, weird stage mechanic everytime as you move forward, like main story. And adding ontop a \"proud\" feeling when you clear higher difficulty, or dive deeper into dissolution hell would be cherry on top of that.\n\nI believe this kind of permanent mode would help with player retention and make the game feel more alive between major updates, especially when this game Major update is 4 months or even longer.\n\nThank you for your hard work on Morimens. I hope the team will consider adding more long-term repeatable content in the future.\n\nPS. ANDDDDD STORY MODE MADNESS DIFFICULTYYYY", "timestamp": "2026-06-19T03:50:50.659000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2026-06-19T04:47:08.811000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "Murphy_satisfy", "emoji_id": "1468258389850193960", "count": 5}, {"emoji": "❤️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 15}, {"emoji": "Celeste_agree", "emoji_id": "1400771815076528258", "count": 4}, {"emoji": "Nautila_think", "emoji_id": "1459077762684948500", "count": 1}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1517376087141908551", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Permanent Repeatable Content for Long-Term Players", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"], "is_thread_starter": true}
